Nikkei down, dollar at 107.68-70 yen mid-afternoon 
The Nikkei stock average of the Tokyo Stock Exchange stood at 20,861.64
points mid-afternoon Friday, down 106.61 points or 0.5 percent.
The dollar was quoted at the same time at 107.68-70 yen, down from
107.90 yen in New York late Thursday and from 108.01-03 yen here
Thursday afternoon.
Against the mark, the US unit was trading at 1.4877, compared with
1.4850 in New York late Thursday and 1.4888-4891 in Tokyo Thursday
afternoon.
